# QoE adjustment detail reveals pattern of aggressive addback characterization
@type: comparison

@compare:
  header: Addback Item | Management Claim | BCG Assessment | Adjustment
  row: Executive severance ($8M) | One-time | Recurring pattern: 3rd executive departure in 4 years | Remove $8M
  row: IT transformation costs ($12M) | Project-related, non-recurring | Recurring capex-like investment in aged systems | Remove $8M (partial)
  row: Litigation settlement ($6M) | Non-recurring | Industry-wide regulatory pressure; likely recurring | Remove $6M
  row: COVID recovery costs ($5M) | One-time | No longer applicable as of 2023 | Remove $5M
  row: Management consulting ($4M) | Special project | Annual run-rate; reflected in normalized overhead | Remove $4M

@exhibit: Exhibit 2 — QoE Adjustment Detail
@source: BCG analysis; review of management accounts, board minutes, and G&A sub-ledger, 2024

@notes: The IT transformation costs addback is the most significant structural issue. It reveals that capex is being expensed to mask the true capex intensity of the business.

